101: ## Phase 2: Persistent Isolate Worker Pool & Paint-Yielding Spinner
102: 
103: ### Rationale:
104: Spawning background thread Isolates dynamically (using one-shot `compute` commands) introduces a small startup latency (20ms–50ms) to load Dart resources and memory heaps. For heavy computational loops, this can add unnecessary overhead.
105: 
106: To solve this, we implement a **Persistent Isolate Worker Pool** (`IsolateWorker`). Spawning a single, long-lived background Isolate thread on startup, the pool keeps a duplex Port connection active. CPU-heavy tasks are dynamically dispatched, queued, and returned instantly over a single persistent channel.
107: 
108: ### The Unified `IsolateWorker` Service (`lib/services/isolate_worker.dart`)
109: This central, platform-safe service will manage background thread pooling:
110: 
111: ```dart
112: import 'dart:async';
113: import 'dart:isolate';
114: import 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';
115: 
116: class IsolateWorker {
117:   static final IsolateWorker _instance = IsolateWorker._internal();
118:   static IsolateWorker get instance => _instance;
119:   IsolateWorker._internal();
120: 
121:   Isolate? _isolate;
122:   SendPort? _sendPort;
123:   final ReceivePort _receivePort = ReceivePort();
124:   final Map<int, Completer<dynamic>> _pendingTasks = {};
125:   int _taskIdCounter = 0;
126:   bool _initialized = false;
127: 
128:   Future<void> init() async {
129:     if (_initialized || kIsWeb) return;
130:     
131:     _isolate = await Isolate.spawn(_workerEntryPoint, _receivePort.sendPort);
132:     
133:     final Completer<SendPort> portCompleter = Completer<SendPort>();
134:     _receivePort.listen((message) {
135:       if (message is SendPort) {
136:         portCompleter.complete(message);
137:       } else if (message is Map) {
138:         final int id = message['id'];
139:         final dynamic result = message['result'];
140:         final dynamic error = message['error'];
141:         
142:         final completer = _pendingTasks.remove(id);
143:         if (completer != null) {
144:           if (error != null) {
145:             completer.completeError(error);
146:           } else {
147:             completer.complete(result);
148:           }
149:         }
150:       }
151:     });
152: 
153:     _sendPort = await portCompleter.future;
154:     _initialized = true;
155:     debugPrint("IsolateWorker: Persistent worker thread successfully established.");
156:   }
157: 
158:   Future<T> execute<T>(String taskType, Map<String, dynamic> params) async {
159:     if (kIsWeb) {
160:       // Browser environment executes tasks synchronously on the main thread safely
161:       return _executeTaskSync(taskType, params) as T;
162:     }
163:     
164:     await init();
165:     final int taskId = _taskIdCounter++;
166:     final completer = Completer<T>();
167:     _pendingTasks[taskId] = completer;
168: 
169:     _sendPort!.send({
170:       'id': taskId,
171:       'type': taskType,
172:       'params': params,
173:     });
174: 
175:     return completer.future;
176:   }
177: }
178: 
179: // 1. Worker thread entrypoint executing in raw OS sandbox
180: void _workerEntryPoint(SendPort mainSendPort) {
181:   final ReceivePort workerReceivePort = ReceivePort();
182:   mainSendPort.send(workerReceivePort.sendPort);
183: 
184:   workerReceivePort.listen((message) {
185:     if (message is Map) {
186:       final int id = message['id'];
187:       final String taskType = message['type'];
188:       final Map<String, dynamic> params = message['params'];
189: 
190:       try {
191:         final result = _executeTaskSync(taskType, params);
192:         mainSendPort.send({
193:           'id': id,
194:           'result': result,
195:         });
196:       } catch (e) {
197:         mainSendPort.send({
198:           'id': id,
199:           'error': e.toString(),
200:         });
201:       }
202:     }
203:   });
204: }
205: 
206: // 2. Synchronous task dispatch table
207: dynamic _executeTaskSync(String type, Map<String, dynamic> params) {
208:   switch (type) {
209:     case 'writeExcel':
210:       return _writeExcelInIsolate(params);
211:     case 'getMatchedSheets':
212:       return _getMatchedSheetsInIsolate(params);
213:     case 'readSheet':
214:       return _readSheetInIsolate(params);
215:     case 'parseSchema':
216:       return _parseSchemaJsonInIsolate(params['jsonStr']);
217:     case 'importMerge':
218:       return _processImportLogicStatic(params);
219:     default:
220:       throw "IsolateWorker: Unknown task type '$type'";
221:   }
222: }
223: ```
224: 
225: ---
226: 
227: ### App Workflows Utilizing the Isolate Pool
228: 
229: #### 1. Large Schema JSON File Parsing (`schema_service.dart`)
230: * **Usage:** Spawns on App Startup & Schema Additions.
231: * **Execution:**
232:   ```dart
233:   final content = await IsolateWorker.instance.execute<Map<String, dynamic>>(
234:     'parseSchema', 
235:     {'jsonStr': fileContentString}
236:   );
237:   ```
238: 
239: #### 2. High-Performance Database Imports (`storage_service.dart`)
240: * **Usage:** Database backups, imports, and B-tree cache merging in `LocalStore.importData`.
241: * **Execution:** Offload cache merges into the Isolate:
242:   ```dart
243:   final result = await IsolateWorker.instance.execute<Map<String, dynamic>>(
244:     'importMerge', 
245:     {'dbName': _dbName, 'data': data, 'currentEntries': currentEntries}
246:   );
247:   ```
248: 
249: #### 3. Excel Workbook Generating & Writing (`workbook_service.dart`)
250: * **Usage:** Triggered when saving sheets, generating Daily/Monthly reports, or finalising a day.
251: * **Execution:** Dispatches sheets and formula tables to the Isolate:
252:   ```dart
253:   final fileBytes = await IsolateWorker.instance.execute<List<int>>(
254:     'writeExcel', 
255:     {'existingBytes': existingBytes, 'data': data, 'sheetName': sheetName}
256:   );
257:   ```
258: 
259: #### 4. Excel Workbook Discovery & Reading (`workbook_service.dart`)
260: * **Usage:** Triggered during report data inspection and loading.
261: * **Execution:** Offloads Excel file tree matches and row mappings:
262:   ```dart
263:   final matchedSheets = await IsolateWorker.instance.execute<List<String>>(
264:     'getMatchedSheets', 
265:     {'bytes': bytes, 'type': type}
266:   );
267:   ```
268:   ```dart
269:   final sheetData = await IsolateWorker.instance.execute<List<List<dynamic>>>(
270:     'readSheet', 
271:     {'bytes': bytes, 'sheetName': sheetName}
272:   );
273:   ```
274: 
275: #### 5. Yielding Delays inside Main Thread (Web Fallback)
276: * **Yielding Delays:** To ensure the spinner paints instantly on Web targets (where the isolate runs synchronously on the main thread), yield execution before heavy operations:
277:   - In `_AggregatorReportViewState._generate()`: Keep yielding delay `await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 150));` after the post-frame callback.
278:   - In `_handleDone` (`_CollectionViewTabState`), append yielding delays immediately after updating progress texts:
279:   ```dart
280:   statusNotifier.value = "Saving database records locally...";
281:   await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 150)); // Yield to paint status text
282:   ```
