{"File":"/home/ruggedcoder/softwares/fresh/anydb_flutter/.chat_context/transcript.jsonl","LineNumber":2093,"LineContent":"{\"step_index\":2123,\"source\":\"MODEL\",\"type\":\"PLANNER_RESPONSE\",\"status\":\"DONE\",\"created_at\":\"2026-05-28T05:26:06Z\",\"thinking\":\"**Observing Web-Specific Handling**\\n\\nI've noticed something in `sqlite_helper.dart` – specific web checks are implemented with early returns. The code checks `if (kIsWeb) return;` or `if (kIsWeb) return [];` in several methods, presumably to avoid execution on web. Yet, the `sqlite3` import remains, along with a nullable `_db` static variable.\\n\\n\\n**Analyzing Transitive Failures**\\n\\nI've realized the compiler still processes import statements and definitions, causing transitive FFI failures on the Web. The `sqlite3` import and nullable `_db` cause problems, even with `kIsWeb` guards. I've been considering two solutions: first, implementing conditional imports using `sqlite_helper_stub.dart` and `sqlite_helper_mobile.dart` for cleaner handling. Alternatively, I'm evaluating using the `sqlite3` package's Web variant, though I'm also considering if we need SQLite on the Web at all.\\n\\n\\n**Refining Conditional Export**\\n\\nI've refined the approach. Instead of conditional imports, conditional *exports* now seem optimal. I'm focusing on creating `sqlite_helper_web.dart` with stub methods, and `sqlite_helper_native.dart` containing the real implementation, both with the same static methods. The core file, `sqlite_helper.dart`, will then conditionally export based on `dart.library.ffi`. This neatly solves the FFI transitive failure by ensuring the web version has no SQLite dependencies, while the native version handles database operations, using FFI. This is incredibly clean!\\n\\n\\n**Implementing Conditional Export**\\n\\nI've confirmed that if `sqlite_helper.dart` conditionally exports, other files importing it don't need changes! I'm now drafting `sqlite_helper_native.dart` as a direct copy of the current implementation, and `sqlite_helper_web.dart` with stub methods and NO `sqlite3` import. `sqlite_helper.dart` will be the conditional exporter. It's an elegant solution!\\n\\n\\n\",\"tool_calls\":[{\"name\":\"write_to_file\",\"args\":{\"ArtifactMetadata\":\"{\\\"ArtifactType\\\":\\\"other\\\",\\\"RequestFeedback\\\":false,\\\"Summary\\\":\\\"Native-specific implementation of SqliteHelper containing package:sqlite3 imports for dynamic FFI database access on desktop and mobile platforms.\\\"}\",\"CodeContent\":\"\\\"import 'dart:convert';\\\\nimport 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';\\\\nimport 'package:sqlite3/sqlite3.dart' as sql;\\\\nimport 'package:path/path.dart' as p;\\\\nimport 'file_service.dart';\\\\n\\\\nclass SqliteHelper {\\\\n  static sql.Database? _db;\\\\n  static final FileService _fileService = FileService();\\\\n\\\\n  static Future\u003csql.Database\u003e get _database async {\\\\n    if (_db != null) return _db!;\\\\n    \\\\n    final root = await _fileService.getInternalRoot();\\\\n    final dbPath = p.join(root, 'anydb_storage.db');\\\\n    await _fileService.ensureDir(root);\\\\n    \\\\n    _db = sql.sqlite3.open(dbPath);\\\\n    return _db!;\\\\n  }\\\\n\\\\n  static Future\u003cvoid\u003e initTable(String dbName) async {\\\\n    if (kIsWeb) return;\\\\n    final db = await _database;\\\\n    final tableName = _fileService.sanitizeName(dbName);\\\\n\\\\n    // Check if the table already exists\\\\n    final tableCheck = db.select(\\\\n      \\\\\\\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table' AND name=?\\\\\\\",\\\\n      [tableName],\\\\n    );\\\\n\\\\n    if (tableCheck.isEmpty) {\\\\n      // Fresh table — create with the new schema directly\\\\n      db.execute('''\\\\n        CREATE TABLE \\\\\\\"$tableName\\\\\\\" (\\\\n          id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\\\n          business_key_value TEXT,\\\\n          is_active INTEGER DEFAULT 1,\\\\n          value TEXT\\\\n        )\\\\n      ''');\\\\n    } else {\\\\n      // Table exists — check columns and migrate if needed\\\\n      final columns = db.select('PRAGMA table_info(\\\\\\\"$tableName\\\\\\\")');\\\\n      final columnNames = columns.map((c) =\u003e c['name'] as String).toSet();\\\\n\\\\n      // Migrate old `key` column to `id`\\\\n      if (columnNames.contains('key') \u0026\u0026 !columnNames.contains('id')) {\\\\n        db.execute('ALTER TABLE \\\\\\\"$tableName\\\\\\\" RENAME COLUMN \\\\\\\"key\\\\\\\" TO \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\"');\\\\n      }\\\\n\\\\n      // Add missing columns from the new schema\\\\n      if (!columnNames.contains('business_key_value')) {\\\\n        db.execute('ALTER TABLE \\\\\\\"$tableName\\\\\\\" ADD COLUMN business_key_value TEXT');\\\\n      }\\\\n      if (!columnNames.contains('is_active')) {\\\\n        db.execute('ALTER TABLE \\\\\\\"$tableName\\\\\\\" ADD COLUMN is_active INTEGER DEFAULT 1');\\\\\\n\u003ctruncated 6153 bytes\u003e\",\"Description\":\"\\\"Create sqlite_helper_native.dart with native SQLite and package:sqlite3 imports.\\\"\",\"IsArtifact\":\"false\",\"Overwrite\":\"true\",\"TargetFile\":\"\\\"/home/ruggedcoder/softwares/fresh/anydb_flutter/lib/services/sqlite_helper_native.dart\\\"\",\"toolAction\":\"\\\"Creating sqlite_helper_native.dart\\\"\",\"toolSummary\":\"\\\"Create sqlite_helper_native.dart\\\"\"}}],\"truncated_fields\":[\"tool_calls\"]}"}
